  "explanation": "The defendant, an accountant with no prior criminal record, abused a position of trust to embezzle $25,000 from their employer. This is a serious offense that warrants a carceral sentence to deter similar conduct and reflect the gravity of the breach of trust. However, significant mitigating factors exist: the defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated remorse and an effort to make amends by partially paying back the stolen funds. Considering these factors, a lenient sentence of 3 months of incarceration is appropriate, followed by a period of supervised release and a mandate to complete full restitution.",
